3_19	0.13929867	The Library of Congress, which by then had about 3,000 volumes, was destroyed.
3_20	0.14250649	With one act, Jefferson became the founder of the Library of Congress as it now exists.
3_21	0.12505675	''I learn from the newspapers that the vandalism of our enemy has triumphed at Washington over science as well as the arts, by the destruction of the public library with the noble edifice in which it was deposited,'' Jefferson wrote in a letter that September.
3_22	0.094131769	By then retired to his home at Monticello, Jefferson offered Congress the opportunity to buy his private library which then totaled nearly 6,500 volumes.
3_23	0.088786543	The purchase was approved.
3_24	0.088046246	The price was almost $24,000.
3_25	0.12390874	Jefferson called it the ''choicest collection of books in the U.S''.
